          exp: "<strong>Unit 94</strong> — специальные relative pronouns: <em>whose, whom, where</em>.<br><br><strong>Whose</strong> (чей) — принадлежность, для людей и вещей:<ul><li><em>the man whose car was stolen</em> — мужчина, у которого угнали машину;</li><li><em>the book whose cover is torn</em> — книга, у которой порвана обложка.</li></ul><strong>Whom</strong> — объектная форма <em>who</em>, формальный стиль, особенно после предлогов:<ul><li><em>the colleague whom I mentioned</em>;</li><li><em>the person to whom I wrote</em> (formal) = <em>the person (who) I wrote to</em> (informal).</li></ul><strong>Where</strong> — для мест:<ul><li><em>the hotel where we stayed</em>;</li><li>эквивалент: <em>the hotel at which we stayed / the hotel (that) we stayed at</em>.</li></ul><strong>When / why</strong> — время/причина: <em>the day when we met, the reason why she left</em>.<br><strong>Предлог + whom/which</strong> в формальном письме: <em>the company for which she works</em>. В разговоре: <em>the company (that) she works for</em>.<p>Не путайте <em>whose</em> с <em>who's</em> (= <em>who is/has</em>).</p>",
