          id: 'int_u129',
          text: 'Unit 129 — Существительное + предлог',
          note: 'a reason for / a lack of / difficulty in',
          unitUrl: 'https://ok-english.ru/unit-129-blue/',
          exp: "<strong>Unit 129</strong> — существительное + предлог: устойчивые сочетания.<br><br><strong>For</strong>: <em>a reason for, a need for, a demand for, a request for</em>. <strong>Of</strong>: <em>a cause of, a photo of, an example of, an advantage of, a lack of</em>. <strong>In</strong>: <em>an increase/rise/fall/drop/decrease in, a change in, difficulty in</em>, <em>interest in, belief in</em>. <strong>To</strong>: <em>damage to, an answer to, a solution to, a reply to, an attitude to/towards, invitation to</em>. <strong>With</strong>: <em>a relationship/connection with, contact with</em>. <strong>Between</strong>: <em>difference between</em>.<br><br>Примеры: <em>There's no reason for worry</em> — нет причин для беспокойства. <em>The cause of the fire is unknown</em> — причина пожара неизвестна. <em>There's been a rise in prices</em> — произошёл рост цен. <em>What's the solution to this problem?</em> — каково решение этой проблемы?<br><br><strong>Пары-ловушки:</strong> <em>cause of</em> ↔ <em>reason for</em> (оба = причина). <em>increase in</em> (не <em>of</em>) при описании параметра, который растёт. После предлога идёт герундий: <em>a reason for leaving early</em>.",
          exc: '<p><em>cause of</em>, но <em>reason for</em>.</p><p><em>an increase/rise/fall in</em> (не <em>of</em>).</p><p><em>damage to</em>, <em>solution to</em>.</p>',
