          note: 'interested in / keen on / satisfied with',
          unitUrl: 'https://ok-english.ru/unit-131-blue/',
          exp: "<strong>Unit 131</strong> — прилагательное + предлог, часть 2.<br><br><strong>With</strong>: <em>angry/annoyed/furious/pleased/happy/satisfied/bored/delighted/disappointed with</em>. <strong>About</strong>: <em>angry/annoyed/worried/upset/excited/happy/nervous about</em>. <strong>In</strong>: <em>interested in, involved in, successful in, experienced in, rich in, weak in</em>. <strong>On</strong>: <em>keen on, dependent on, based on</em>. <strong>To</strong>: <em>married to, engaged to, similar to, close to, related to, kind/nice/rude/polite to, opposed to, addicted to</em>. <strong>By</strong>: <em>surprised/shocked/impressed/amazed/astonished by/at</em>.<br><br>Примеры: <em>I'm not interested in politics</em> — политика меня не интересует. <em>She's married to a doctor</em> — она замужем за врачом. <em>He was very kind to me</em> — он был очень добр ко мне.<br><br><strong>Противопоставления:</strong> <em>angry with sb</em> (на человека) ↔ <em>angry about sth</em> (из-за ситуации). <em>tired of</em> = надоело ↔ <em>tired from</em> = устал от (нагрузки). <em>interested in</em> (долгий интерес) ↔ <em>interesting to sb</em> (интересно кому-то).",
