          note: 'Verb + object + complement / adjective',
          unitUrl: 'https://ok-english.ru/unit-28-green/',
          exp: '<strong>Unit 28</strong> (Advanced) — дополнения после глаголов: типы комплементации.<br><br>Глаголы выбирают структуру своего дополнения. Основные паттерны:<ul><li><strong>Verb + object + noun (object complement):</strong> <em>They elected him president; We call him Bob.</em></li><li><strong>Verb + object + adjective:</strong> <em>She painted the door red; I find this book fascinating; He drove me crazy.</em></li><li><strong>Verb + object + infinitive (с to):</strong> <em>She asked him to help; I want you to listen.</em></li><li><strong>Verb + object + bare infinitive</strong> (после <em>make, let, have</em> + глаголы восприятия): <em>Let me go; I saw him leave.</em></li><li><strong>Verb + object + -ing:</strong> <em>I heard her singing; I saw them running.</em></li><li><strong>Verb + object + past participle:</strong> <em>I want it done by noon; She had her car repaired.</em></li></ul><br><strong>Разница полное vs неполное восприятие:</strong> <em>I saw him cross the street</em> (видел целиком) vs <em>I saw him crossing the street</em> (увидел в процессе).<br><br><strong>Семантика «объектного предикатива»:</strong> <em>elect, appoint, name, call, consider, find, declare, prove, keep, leave</em> + object + complement образуют «маленькое предложение» внутри главного: <em>I consider him [a friend] / [honest] / [to be reliable].</em><br><br><strong>Регистр:</strong> <em>consider/find sb to be + adj</em> формальнее, чем без <em>to be</em>.',
