          exp: "<strong>Unit 70</strong> — прилагательные с <em>to</em>-inf, <em>-ing</em> и <em>that</em>-clause.<br><br><strong>Явление:</strong> прилагательные требуют специфичных комплементов; смешение ведёт к ошибкам.<br><br><strong>Модели:</strong><ul><li>Adj + <em>to</em>-inf: <em>able, eager, reluctant, willing, likely, unlikely, due, liable, keen, happy, ready</em>: <em>She was eager to learn.</em></li><li>Adj + prep + <em>-ing</em>: <em>capable of doing, fond of reading, interested in learning, afraid of failing, tired of waiting, good at singing</em>.</li><li>Adj + <em>that</em>-clause: <em>sure that, certain that, aware that, convinced that, surprised that, sorry that, glad that</em>.</li><li>Оценочные с формальным <em>it</em>: <em>It is kind of you to help. It is difficult for us to decide.</em></li></ul><strong>Примеры:</strong><ul><li><em>I'm afraid of flying.</em> — Я боюсь летать.</li><li><em>He's keen to start / keen on starting.</em> — двойная модель для <em>keen</em>.</li></ul><strong>Контраст:</strong> <em>sorry to + inf</em> (о будущем действии) vs <em>sorry for -ing</em> (о прошлом действии). <em>Good at</em>, а не <s>good in</s>. Предлоги при прилагательных — часть лексического минимума C1.",
